The last three decades have seen numbers in England and Wales rising more sharply than ever, almost doubling to today’s level of about 85,000. The latest figures again show (19) _______ in Western Europe. Prisons are massively overcrowded, while chronic staff shortages mean staff cannot even ensure safety.
We need to take a hard look at sentencing policy. The increased use of minimum sentences has tied judges’ hands, (20) _______ and discretion to adopt alternatives to prison where appropriate.
Unless the Government gets prisoner numbers down and devotes the resources necessary (21) _______, building a renewed prison estate and providing effective education, training and other purposeful activity in every prison, all they will be doing is (22) _______ to staunch gaping wounds.